column5: Had a nice day on Simcoe today.  Terry met us this morning and we headed out to a few fave spots.  The travel was the pits with lots of ruts from 4 wheelers in the slush that had frozen up.  Made for slow going and took the sliders off of Paul's hut  Here's Terry's set up:        Here's Paul's new hut.  Very roomy inside, wish I had taken a pic of the inside        I was nice and comfy in my little hut        Had lots of action, but hardly any takers.  I finally landed a nice one, and it was the only one landed of the day.  I was pretty happy        And I caught it using one of TJ's jigheads from his store, so I bet he will be happy.  Too bad my camera decided to freeze up on me.      Anyhow, we fished til 2 p.m. and had several on and off, but just the one for the day.  Looking forward to next weekend out there.  Hope the ice conditions are a bit better, but it was at least thick enough now!  Great company once again Terry, hope to see you next weekend
That's fantastic, Joey! Glad you had a good day. UMMMM Trout for supper?
Still looked like a fun day!Nice fish and that hut of yours is nice. After yesterday a portable hut is defineatly in the near future.
Terry was with you.. something got broken.. and you're surprised???

hey, I resemble that ...  was a good time but one heck of a ride....my back needs a little R&R....  oh and no dead whitefish were seen on my underwater camera...some people are saying hundreds of dead whities from vhs...

Yes, trout for supper Roy  Davey buoy, they are a lifesaver on days like today.  I used to love fishing outside, but you can stay out much longer in a heated hut.  We use our walkie talkies to converse.  Wayne, I never thought of that   Ya, my back is done too Terry, time for a nap I think

The perfect size Laker for the B- B- Q, right there,  Looks like the Slush has tightened up!!  I guess you can blame me for some of those 4 wheeler ruts!!!  Pauls hut looks fantastic!! He should try some UHMW Plastic for runners.  Terry aka 'Columbo' Good news re no dead Whities
Came in at 25 inches Rick.  I'm sure Paul will read your comment on the sliders, thanks!!  Oh, and yes, thanks for the ruts  #&$@
Wasnt too bad out. Thought the winds were going to be a problem with my pop up. We walked a bit over 3 km lol, marked lots but no takers
Nice fish Joey!
Glad you had some success, great looking fish,  sorry about the damage but it still looks like it was a better day than at work
nice fish - and good loooking hut, almost looks warn in there.
gopro at 104 ft can see the orange head on the jig      my underwater camera doing a 360 looking for dead fish , live fish or anything else
I can't believe Terry how clear that camera is at that depth. That's wild!!!!
Very nice, Laker, Hut & Camera view Tight Lines SBK
Right on very nice fish. I've yet to catch one of those myself...still hunting. Thanks for sharing, nice report.
Well ill be out all week so will let you know if I find a hot spot. Glad to see you got one.  You had the I'm not Terry sign out lol
Well go get em Lloyd.  Hot spots would be good    We only tried two old spots today and the one produced!
Nice of you to show up the guys J.  Just got in. Will work on a report soon. I got a first,and am in need of a shower after walking miles today.
Way to go Joey, at least you caught one. I've got to get out there again, hoping the walk is better than my last trip out in a foot of water-slush.
Great report Joey!!  Thanks a million!
